\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid11798551 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Now, you were born in 1893?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Whereabouts was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 In New Street, Longton, Stoke on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Trent{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1008\li1008\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1008\itap0\pararsid12133791 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
What sort of houses were they?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid11798551 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh very small, one bedroom and one living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you a scullery or kitchen at the back then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, no. All in. Only two roomed house. It is demolished now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 So what had you downstairs - a big room with a kitchen range in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 That's all, yes, to boil a kettle. To do all the cooking, yes. And the rent was about half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you a sink in that room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 A sink? Yes. Everything was done in the one room downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you any garden outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No garden, no garden, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 A back yard?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 A communal yard. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And had you a cellar at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 That must have been very squashed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Very primitive, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How many of you were there in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 At that time there were only three of us, mother, father and meself. I was the eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you sleep upstairs in your parents' bedroom then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, yes. One bedroom. Then we moved from there after about two years, when the family began to get bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Where did you move to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 We moved to, only about two hundred yards away to another terrace type house which had a bit better accommodation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How big was that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 That had a front room, a living room, and two bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I see. How many children were there by that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Two. And we didn't stay there long. We moved to Derbyshire when I was four years old. I begun school then, I begun school when I was two and a half. School at 
two and a half and when I was four years old we moved to a place called Swadlincote in Derbyshire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Why did you move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 We moved owing to shortage of work, me father was a carpenter. In the building trade and we moved there because there was some 
work going. That would be about thirty-six miles away from the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Potteries{\*\xmlclose}
, Swadlincote, and we stayed there about two years where we had another addition to the family, that was three children by then, by the time I was seven. Then we came back to Longton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 After work again I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Yes, the work had finished and me father came back and we went to a better type house this time, still in Longton, and by that time I was about seven, and we had another brother, and then a sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How big was that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
That was a bigger house, a similar terrace type house, it is still there, I saw it the other week, still there, but closed, ready for demolition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How many rooms were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 That was, oh only two bedrooms. There were not many thre
e bedroomed houses in those days, and that was just about the end of the South African War, in 1900 then, I was born in 1893, it was about 1900.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you stay there for any length of time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, then we moved into about another couple of yards awa
y to another small house, smaller than that, one living room and a kitchen and two bedrooms. And then we moved about a lot in the locality. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 
You can imagine, things were very, very poor, there was not much money about, although my father was a tradesman we didn't get a lot of money and the family was growing up then. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
The wages were about 30/- a week for a tradesman, and the labourers used to get about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid71331 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 1 a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You were moving round very often then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Quite a lot, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you move, did you have a horse and cart, or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Yes. Yes. Sometimes me father would carry some of the furniture when we didn't have to move very far away. We moved as I say very frequent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How about when you went to Swadlincote then, how did you manage that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 The furniture went by train, I remember my mother telling me. That went by railway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you all go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh we went by train. I can remember going there when I was about four. I can remember going to school at Swadlincote. And I remember com
ing back again. I came back again, I was about seven years of age. And I went to various schools in the town, perhaps every, I changed schools twice in one year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 It must have had an unsettling effect on you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Unsettling, yes, well I have always been like that. Yes, I think that's what's done it. I want to get back to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} now!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Your schooling was interrupted by all these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, I don't know whether it made any difference really because I was never backward, I always we
nt forward. Oh I never stayed in one class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You enjoyed school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What were your favourite subjects?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well. I liked them all actually. I think I was about the, er equal in all the subjects at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were they strict with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 Yes, very. very strict. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Of course the cane was used very frequent in the schools, oh yes. But it had a salutary effect upon you, you knew who the master was, I will say that. It er, in my experience I don't think it did any harm at al
l. Discipline. Oh no. No. You have got to respect the teachers like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And how old were you when you finished school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you have stayed on if you had had an opportunity?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh yes, yes. I should have stayed on. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 At the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Queens{\*\xmlclose} of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Hollinsonberry{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 but owing to the labour position again father said I had got to start to work.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 They needed your wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 They needed the wage. We needed everything and me being the eldest, and at that time there were eight children then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would it affect you very much when every new baby arrived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, no. No, not at all. We always welcomed a new addition somehow. We didn't, as far as I know, no-one objected. We didn't object.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 There was no jealousy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, no jealousy, not in our family anyhow. There were two sisters and six brothers at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had your mother any help when the babies were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, no help with the children or the house, no. Mother did it all, she stayed at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had she worked at all before her marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, she worked in a pottery factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of job did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
When she was a girl she was a handle maker. A cup handle maker. And her wages, she used to tell me, was 2d. for making twenty dozen cup handles! 
That worked out at 1/- a day. Twenty times a score. So 2d. for a score. Not per twenty, per dozen. Twenty dozen. And Mother didn't go to work again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 She had enough on at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 She had enough yes. Keep the house tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you help her much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, she trained us how to do the housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh I could clean all the fireplace out and clean the floors. Scrub the floors and clean it out, dust round, or all of us could do that because Mother trained us.
 And she was a good cook. She used to make, the money go out of a few shillings because there would only be about a pound a week coming in then, in those days that I am talking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you shops near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Shops near. Yes. Always shops very near. Didn't have to spend any fares to do your shopping, no. The district was full of shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Was there a market?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Always been a market in this town, yes. Very good market.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your mother buy things from the market?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes on Saturdays. We us
ed to walk down to the market on Saturday which is only a few hundred yards away from where we lived, the market is still there now, it has been up about ninety years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you have meat every day or only on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, not many times a week. Probably twice, a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of meals would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Very very sparse really. Example for breakfast you wouldn't have much, perhaps a bit of toast and a cup of tea and then go to school. There was no school dinners, you would come home for
 your bit of lunch, that comprised perhaps a drop of soup, with some bread in, or a cheap cut of meat, about 2d. a pound, that was, Mother used to make a stew, perhaps a pudding that she used to make.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How about your evening meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well we used to have perhaps something for tea but not a lot again, very rarely we used to have anything after tea, hot supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What would your father have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well he was out of work all day and then he used to have his see when he came home, he used to carry o
ut sandwiches with him to work and come home and have his dinner at home, in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of meal would he have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 He would perhaps have a bit of meat. Or chop. Or something like that, perhaps something similar to what we had mid-day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had your father any outside interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Only one, I am sorry to say, and that was the public house. Yes. Although he was, my father was an athlete, he used to do professional running, although he used to drink, he used to run for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid71331 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 5, or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid71331 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 10 or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid71331 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 20, in this area, and he was a good footballer and cricketer, that was before we were grown up, when he was in his twenties and thirties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had he any interest in Unions or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Unions yes. My father was a trade unionist. Yes. The woodworkers, the Associated Society of woodworkers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I see. And was he interested actively?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Actively, in the Trade Union movement. No, very little. He was a Conservative in politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How about your mother, did she ever go out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Mother? No. Mother was rather more religious type. Used to quote the Bible. Read the Bible. Every day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Was she a chapel goer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, Mother was a very placid type. Father was, he was different from Mother really. They weren't of the same temperament at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would she send all of you to Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, we always used to go to Sunday School. Yes. We used to go to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 
Wesleyan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485  Chapel Sunday School. Every Sunday morning and afternoon. We got prizes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 All of you went? All the family and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes. And Father used to attend the Bible Class, he was a member of the Bible Class for a period of years and then he'd stop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you any Sunday School outings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, yes. We used to go Sunday School outings, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Where would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
We went more locally. We used to go, one chapel in Longton, we used to go in a furniture van, pulled by a horse and cart, to go up to Lightwood, on the way to Rough Close and have a tea party and races, etc. Yes, we used to 
go to have the treats there, Sunday School outings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you say you were strictly brought up as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of things would they be strict about, what were you made to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Made to do? To tell the truth, or else!
 Yes, we used to have thrashings from Father if we just didn't do what we were told. Only punished by Father, not Mother. Mother never, no Mother was a placid type as I say, she could talk to us. When we were children you see. Until we'd grown up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were they strict over table manners at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 We were brought up properly, yes. Strict table manners. Yes. And they'd say grace. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Who said it, your Mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you any newspapers or books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Not many. Sometimes we'd have an evening paper. I don't remember very often having a daily paper, the morning paper, not while I was a juvenile, while I went to school. But afterwards we did, when I was growing up and starting to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you a Sunday paper at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, I think, yes, I think Father used to have a Sunday paper. But we didn't read it. Not at er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Weren't you allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, they was a bit strict on reading the Sunday papers and we were told not to read them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You were saying that your mother read the Bible, was there anything else she would read?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 Very, very few books. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
The few books, yes we had a few books. "John Halifax, Gentleman," we used to read. You know that one? Yes, we had books in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Any other titles you recall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Er - yes. Prizes from school. We used to read. And we used to have Dickens books in the house. Charles Dickens "Oliver Twist" and others. Then we began to understand what we were, that was up to the age of perh
aps nine, and when I was ten I passed an examination to go to a higher school and I was there three years and that's what brought me out. I think I learned more in the three years that I had done in the previous ten, seven rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 A good school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Very good, with a very good headmaster, very strict. Strict disciplinarian. All the staff were strict but all for our own good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Made things interesting did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Made us interest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 ed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485  yes. It was a very good headmaster, Mr. Last. From then we began to grow up, from that school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How large a school was it? In those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Large. Oh, this school where I went, Queensbury, was a mixed school of boys and girls in the same class. Well it was, I think that was built as an experiment becaus
e it hadn't been built when I went there, less than ten years I believe. And I should say about probably three hundred, went there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How many in a class would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well I should say about forty I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Fairly big?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes. Boys 
and girls in the same class. And it was a higher education that was. That was the school. We begun to learn things from there. We were more adult then than what the older children were at the ordinary elementary schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were your friends from that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 My friends yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I wondered actually if you were moving around so much whether you would lose contact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I see, well actually there was five of us friends and we went, we went from elementary school and from there we passed the examinat
ion and all five of us passed together and we stayed together in the same class all the time, and out of those five there's only one living besides meself, and I met him last year. He was one of the five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 From a similar sort of background were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh better background than meself actually. And we used to go in each other's houses and call for each other when we went to school.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How about after school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 After School? No, not very often. We used to meet in the morning. We always went to school together. At the last school, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Queensbury{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, 'till we all left school together. And before we left we all passed another scholarship the College of Preceptors Exam, to go to college, that was going to be Trentham, where the Duke of Sutherland l
eft Trentham Hall because he said the River Trent, the River Trent wanted dredging and he said it wasn't fit to live there and he offered Trentham Hall to the then County Borough of Stoke on Trent to be used as a college. That was about 1905, or 1906. And
 
after considering it the Education Committee turned it down, so we didn't go. I was twelve years old at the time when I passed the exam. That was a sore blow, that was a blow, because that's what we wanted to do. Because we wanted to go to be teachers. An
d
 then when time for me to leave school our headmaster suggested we go to the Pupil Teacher Centre in Longton until we were sixteen years of age when we would become teachers. Uncertificated teachers. And we didn't take it up because I had to start to work
 and my friends started to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 They started work as well, even though they were from slightly better off families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes. Slightly better off yes. Although they were all artisan families. But they were slightly better off. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did your parents think of your friends? Were there any sort of families that they didn't want you to associate with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did my parents view my friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, would your mother say "Don't play with those children" or?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Not very often. They trusted u
s to do what we were told before we went. And we didn't get into any trouble, as far as I know, not any serious trouble or police trouble. We used to go out for long walks, miles for walks, perhaps ten or twelve miles. Back home again. That was in our, ju
st about the time we were leaving school. The age of thirteen and fourteen. Yes. Well we were growing up then and I started to work. At a pottery factory, running moulds, at the then price of 6/- per week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What exactly were you doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I worked wi
th a man who was a saucer maker and I worked a ten hour day for 6/- a week and ten hours a day from Monday to Friday and then about five hours on a Saturday, for 6/- a week. And I had to assist the saucer maker by taking the moulds in the drying shed and 
then fetching others out and taking the saucers off and fetching the clay and taking all the scraps back into the slip house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you find that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 That was very hard work, more or less slavery in those days. No breaks, no tea breaks, only dinner times for an hour break until 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the evening. The hours were about seven, or 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}half past seven{\*\xmlclose}
 in the morning until six in the evening without any breaks only one breaks for dinner. An hour.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How far away from home was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh rou
ghly round about, not far, half a mile away, ten minutes walk. But we used to stay to dinner, one or two sandwiches that's all we had then. And make our tea on the factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How large a concern was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh very small factory, the first one. Then I worked in a larger factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How long after was that, how long were you at your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh about a year, then perhaps a year at a larger factory where I got 7/6d. a week then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 A similar job was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 A similar job yes, but a heavier 
job. Working with a, a similar job but heavier, by reason of the man was making plates, large plates, which made it heavier work and more clay to use and we had to carry the clay from the slip house to the man who was making the plates. That was until I w
as about sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Then I went into the building trade as a carpenter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Why did you switch from working in the pottery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well it wasn't leading anywhere and I wasn't learning a trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Whose idea was it? Your father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 My idea, no my idea. Because I wanted to get on a bit better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you get your job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh by applying to a builder. A large builders in used to go there Hanley. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 That was at 2 and a half pence,1/2d an hour which equalled about 11/- a week.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I see. And what exactly were you doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh working in the workshop as a joiner. Making things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Apprentice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Apprentice, making things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You started learning a trade then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Learning the trade, yes. Learning the trade of carpenter and joiner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And how long were you with that firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh with that firm, a few years. 'Till I got married. I was married when I was twenty-one. (1914)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you known your wife a long time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, I knew my wife about six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you first meet her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well by that time I had left home and gone to live with me grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Where did she live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 She lived at Fenton in a small business. And I went to live with me grandmother and my wife was in service at t
he, next door business. That's where I mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Why had you actually left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
I left home because I was, I was not satisfied with the home conditions and I was growing up and I thought I could make a better life for meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I suppose it was still in a smallish house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 A better house at that time but at the same time things were very poor altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you handed all your wage over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes. I used to hand all my wages over to Mother, Mother used to have the wages. And then she
 used to give me pocket money such as 6d. a week or 1/- a week when I got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well I didn't smoke. Oh, perhaps a Boys Paper. 1d. Or a few sweets. Then cinemas began to open up then. And we'd perhaps go to the cinem
as for 2d. By that time that was bringing us towards the Great War and then I proposed to my wife to get married, she agreed and we were married when the Great War started. The War had started 1914 and we were married on St. Valentine's Day 1915, so we en
joyed our Golden Wedding three years ago.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were you married at Church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 We were married in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}parish{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} of Fenton, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Fenton{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Parish{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of a wedding was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Fairly quiet, very quiet. Yes. We walked to church an
d walked back again and there was several couples getting married that day, including a man who was in the Army, a service man, he was getting married that day, and we didn't have much fuss. In the evening we went to a place where we lived for a time, qui
te near to my grandmother's home, my grandmother couldn't look after us at her place so we got lodgings opposite, the other side of the road, in Fenton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you saved up at all before you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, we didn't save up, I remember I had abou
t 30/- when we got married. I bought the ring and we didn't have anything special in the way of clothing, our best clothes. And my wife was still doing domestic work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 After you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 After we got married, yes. Nine weeks after we got married I joined the Army.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How much were you earning when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I was earning about 32 or 33 shillings a week. My wife was earning about 7/- a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You had fairly good wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, because I was a tradesman. That was about the top wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Was it fairly easy finding a job in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 
No, it was very difficult in those days in the building trade in the Potteries because after the industrial revolution the properties were all built, houses and shops, and they weren't too old then and there wasn't much building being done.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were you out of work ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
No, not before I was married. Worked pretty frequently but there was no unemployment pay not until 1912. When I was eighteen and being in the building trade I had
 to pay to that because the Unemployment Act came out for the building trade workers because they used to lose a lot of time in the winter owing to the bad weather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, I see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 The Unemployment Exchanges were open then from 1912 onwards, but not
 for everybody, it was only meant for the engineers and building trade workers, until after the war had ended. I went into the Army and I was in the Army four years, served overseas, was wounded twice and gassed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did your wife manage during your absence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 My wife during that time was working. She was living on the 12/- a week she had allowance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 In lodgings was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, mostly. And then she went to live with her parents, during part of the war, the latter part of the year, when I was overseas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you any leave at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
I used to get leave from the Army, yes, I was lucky to get leave each Christmas. As it happened I was just lucky to get leave then and I was abroad in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Belgium
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} when the war ended. And I was home in time for Christmas 1918 again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 So what happened after the war ended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
After the war we really started then to create a home. But we couldn't get any accommodation only where, living with my in-laws who were very kind, nice people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 It's not like having a home of your own though, is there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
We wanted a home of our own but there was no houses to be let. Not then. Because the war was over and everybody wanted to get a home of their own and we didn't get a home of our own for fifteen years from the time we were married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 One, a son, he were born in 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What is your son's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 He's in the aircraft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What about your brothers and sisters, what sort of jobs did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Three of them went into the coal mines. After working in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 potteries}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
. In the pottery factories, they went to work in the coal mines. And then during the Coal Strike the 1921 Coal Strike, one brother was killed. My eldest sister went, after she left school, went in service. In a bus
iness, in a shop, domestic service. And my youngest sister went to work as an apprentice decorator in a china factory where she served her apprenticeship in a factory, a gilder, decorator.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How about the other brothers, you said three went down the mines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Yes, three of them went down the mines. Ones recently retired after working about 45 years. And another brother worked a good many years and then he came out of the coal mine and had a job in a factory. And a younger brother went to work in a fac
tory and he recently died. And another younger brother, he became a carpenter. And he's still working but he is retiring this year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You said your grandmother had a business in Fenton. What sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 My grandmother had a business in Fenton, it was a dining room, cook shop and dining rooms.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had your grandfather died or was he still alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
My grandfather had died, my grandfather had died then, but I don't remember my maternal grandfather because he died when he was comparatively young, before I was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you any idea what sort of job they had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Yes. My mother's father was a potter, he was a printer. And he met, he was very ill and he died about the age of 45. My paternal grandfather was a joiner, a carpenter, and he died when he was in his sixties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 So carpentry went in your family didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Was in my family. My grandfather came from Leek about 100 years ago, at that time, and met my grandmother and that started his family from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 What was your parents' attitude when you had left home and moved away, were they against it or?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
No, no. No. There was no trouble. But I used to go to see my parents every week, very often oftener than that. We were still very good friends. And I thought it was better for me to s
trike out meself, being the eldest, there would be more room then for the younger ones in the family. We'd been a very close family together, never had any trouble, always been friendly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You said you were usually in fairly small houses, only two bedrooms - where did you all sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Well that was a problem. My mother and father used to have one bedroom and perhaps one or two would perhaps sleep in their room and the others would sleep in the other bedroom, probably two or three to a bed in small r
ooms. The girls would sleep in their mother's bedroom. But the girls didn't sleep with the boys, not in the same room. Then when I left, that made a bit more room, then while the war was on my other two brothers joined the Army, that made more room then i
n the house for my two sisters who were then growing up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were your parents strict over bedtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes. We didn't keep late hours. Around {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the evening would be bedtime. We were taught that old saying "Early to bed, early to rise, mak
es a man healthy, "Healthy and wise" and we used to have to go to bed about eight or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}nine o'clock
{\*\xmlclose} and sleep until seven or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
 in the morning. Mother was always quoting sayings such as "Spare the rod and spoil the child", "Too many cooks spoil the broth", "A }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
ird in hand is worth two in the bush" all of which were true. By quoting these old sayings we got to know them and we used to repeat them in the house. Yes, you can understand we lived very frugally. We didn't have anything at all to throw aw
ay. In fact we used to have clothes given to us, and food as well at times. So then we understood what poverty was. Then we all said that given the chance, we wouldn't live in such poverty as we were doing in that particular period and we didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would your mother make your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Mother used to, yes, make do and men. Cut down and all that. Mother was very good with the needle and cotton. Yes. She didn't have a machine, she used to do it by hand, mending and patching. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you manage over baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 A big zinc bath, yes, we used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you heat the water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh by the copper. That we used to hot the water for washing in, for Mother's washing. Pour it in the zinc bath and then empty it out again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Once a week would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh no, we used to bath oftener than that. Specially if it was warm weather. No that was on the go every day usually for somebody. "Cleanliness is next to Godliness" that's what my mother used to quote to us. She was very fond of quoting
 sayings and extracts from the Bible. Because she was religious Christian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 After you started work, what would you spend your weekends doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well, mostly out in the open air. We used to go and play games outside, or athletics, or there was alway
s something to do. We used to be all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 athletically}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
 minded and we used to know all about "man know thyself." Keep your body fit. We used to practice that. No running after girls.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No? How about after you met your wife thought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well she was the only one I courted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you have evenings out with her when you were courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Yes, most evenings. Even when she was in service, perhaps I'd go round to where she was, still I only knew her six months. In Fenton. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What was your parents opinion of your thinking of getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh they didn't mind at all, no. My wife was very practical a very practical woman. Brought up in a large family similar to our own.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Same sort of background?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Very similar. My wife's father worked down the coal mines. He was an ostler down the coal mines that looked after the pit ponies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I have heard of people doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 My wife's mother was a very domesticated woman, she had been in service herself until she was married, and then she used
 to teach my wife and my wife could look after the children, she were the eldest of her family, and they had a large family of about eight, and when they came along my wife used to look after the young ones.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 After you started work, were you ever involved with Unions or politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Well, interested. Very interested. But not involved, personally. I used to think that the working man had a raw deal. I was more inclined to Socialism than my father who was a Trade Unionist, he called himself a T
rade Unionist. And when John Ward came to this area in 1906 I used to follow him about. I was about, I was thirteen years old at the time and he came to Stoke and became M.P. for a good many years. And he stood for Socialist Labour Liberal his policy was.
 
And we used to think that we wouldn't do any good until we had a Socialist Government in this country because of the poor conditions which we lived in and which we worked under. And that didn't come to pass until about 1922 when the first Labour Governmen
t was formed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were the unions very strong in the building trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, yes. Yes. Yes. Nearly all the craftsman were a member of a trade union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you get on with the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well not very well I am afraid because the employers r
eally wanted more than you could produce. They were always asking for more. So much so that work became more of a drag than a pleasure, in those days. They were always asking for more. There was not very good relations between employer and employee. That 
book was written by a Socialist "The Ragged Trousered Philanthropist"
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Have you read that book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were things any better after the war? Or was it much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes. I think the result of the war caused a lot of improvement in as much as the w
orker began more to assert himself, especially those men who had served overseas in the Army on active service. They became a little more independent, fighting more for their rights, what they called their rights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you get on with the other people that you worked with, all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, by and large. Yes. Because it was as though nearly everybody felt the same over the problems of the day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 One of the things I didn't get sorted out was how your brothers and sisters were spaced out. You said there were eight children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And you were ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 The eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were they spaced out at yearly intervals or ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, I see
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 That's the sort of ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I know. Well, I were the eldest, and then there was a brother a
 year younger than me, and then another brother, six younger, six years younger than me. They were spaced out like that (..) \{BLANK\}
 would be about five or six years younger than the other one, and, er, two sisters, one was born when I was sixteen, and the younger one was born when I was twenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 So they were spaced out over ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Over a period of, er, o-, over a period of twenty odd years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What did your sister's husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well, one, my sister's husband, one worked in a coalmine, and one was a potter, in the pottery trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Have you any idea how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, he was 22.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had he always been a carpenter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 He didn't ever have any other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did he every do any part-time jobs or casual jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no, father was against that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 He thought he'd done enough when he'd been to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Was he ever out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes. Very frequent, mm, very frequent out of work, nearly, nearly every winter, the building trade, er, were very bad for that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 So how did your mother make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Yes, that's, er, that's a leading question, 'twas, er, terrible the way she had to spend a few shillings, because until, er, 1912 there was
 no unemployment exchange, but that came out in 1912, and I was eighteen years of age, and I joined it. My father was, er, (..) \{BLANK\} so, before then, er, well, people did the best they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Your parents didn't ever have any help from the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Er, no, no, I remember, I remember that, I remember my parents didn't, but, er, a lot of people did around where we were living, oh, yes. The only help we had was when my brother next to me contracted, er,..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Something like tuberculosis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, similar, but it wasn't called that, pneumonia, something like that, and the doctor gave him (..) \{BLANK\} paper for some (..) \{
BLANK\} That's what you had to have, that was his diet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15496509\charrsid15749485 , t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 hat was, er, that was on the doctor's recommendation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 But every winter almost, your father would have a period out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Prac-, practically every winter, yes, because in this area there was very little, er, building being done. There was, er, several small firms but they didn't have much to do, not much building at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, mother was, er, a year older than me father, 23.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did she ever work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, yes, er, a little, in the, er, pottery industry. She did, er, only an odd day, 
odd day, er, in the warehouse, and that, that was about, I remember that was about one and sixpence for that, one day's work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 About how often..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How often? Oh, perhaps, er, oh, (..) \{BLANK\} she could, perhaps, er, yes, perhaps three or four weeks in succession.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Who would look after you children, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, well, we looked after ourselves, we were, er, there weren't any, er, (..) \{BLANK\}
 no babies, she wouldn't like to leave, er, babies, you see, to be looked after, and I know all this because I'm the eldest, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your mother have a set household routine? Did she always do the cleaning one day, and the washing one day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No. No, I don't think she did, no. A lot of people do, I know. My wife doesn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your mother always make your family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, she, er, she used to make do, yes. Er, out of some perhaps we had given to us. (..) \{BLANK\}
 don't remember buying, er, many clothes before I started to work, not, no, not many, no, things were really bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How would she manage over shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Yes, well, well, sometimes we went to a second hand shop to buy shoes perhaps for fourpence a pair or a second hand coat or something like that. You see that was in the first half of the twentieth century, the early 
part, 1900, I was 7 in 1900 even, you see, when the South African war finished and I've got a vivid recollection of these things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your father ever help your mother with jobs about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would he mend shoes or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
No, and, no, and never did, I never remember him doing anything like that. He perhaps, er, do something, er, with his tools. He made her a large kitchen }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 table once}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 , see, anything like that, and he used to make coffins, undertaking, he did that when he was out of work sometimes, see, oh, yes, that'd be if he wasn't working (..) \{BLANK\}
 they'd come in and order for a funeral, father used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your brothers and sisters help in the house }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 at all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, yes, we all, er, mother used to train us to do housework, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Ooh, excepting washing, we could do anything else, cleaning, oh, yes, and polishing, oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Being the eldest, did you have to look after the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 More or less, I was, er, in charge of, er, any younger ones, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You moved round a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Which is the house that you have most memories of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, well, really, I suppose it'd be the later one before I left home myself, er, oh, it was a big windowed house, poor locality really.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Whereabouts was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
That was in Longton, and then I, I was, er, about, er, seventeen or eighteen when we went to live there and I, I left home at 20, then I got married when I was 21.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 In this house at Longton..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 .. how many rooms were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Ah, think there was, there was three bedrooms, and a large, it was a large windowed house, twice as big as an ordinary house, large windowed house, been pulled down no
w, and that meant it was a big front room, and a big front room, bedroom, there were three bedrooms (..) \{BLANK\} in poor condition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Where would you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, we had our meals in the living room, downstairs, and we used to use the front room to sit in, er, later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you ever have meals in your front room, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no, no, people didn't, people didn't have their meals..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did all the family sit down to breakfast at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, well, it's according if, when we were all at home, yes, and then, er, if we were (..) \{BLANK\}
 start to work, well, we'd go out with, er, just a bite and a cup of tea and away to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you ever come home for your {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, sometimes, yes, according to how you were working, oh, yes, (..) \{BLANK\}
 my brother worked on a pottery factory, well he'd, he'd come home to dinner because it wasn't very far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your mother bake her own bread at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, well, she has done, but she didn't, not regularly, 
but she did know how to, to bake bread, yes, she was, er, a good plain cook, could make, er, the money go out very economically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would she ever make jam, or bottled fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No. No, she didn't do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You didn't ever have a garden, did you, at any of these houses?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, a garden? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 
Er, yes, one, we had a garden in one house, we lived in, er, in Derbyshire, near Swadlingcote, yes (..) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 \{BLANK\} yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I was wondering if you ever grew vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, er, no, no, never did have, they were all, er, (..) type house with a back yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What was your parents' attitude over meals? Would they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 let you}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485  talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no father was strict on that, no, he'd, er, he'd say, get on with your food, don't talk. He was very strict in some things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your mother expect you to eat all that she gave you, or could you ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well, we did, we did, things were so bad we never left anything. We could always make room for more in those d-, days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Could you have a second helping or was..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, if there was any over, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Could you bring books or toys to the table, or would they be against this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, oh, no, you could do that, yes. My mother was (..) but father was more strict on things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you have to ask when you could leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes. They were strict on things like that, father was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would anybody ever say grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, mother used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were you a family that always sat at the same places at table, or ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 .. was it a haphazard thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, it was haphazard, more or less. No certain places for the table, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your mother feed the younger ones first or separately, or would you help to feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Ah, mother, mother would fee
d, er, the young ones separately, and we, er, we'd get on with ours and mother used to feed, er, the, the youngest separately, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Very, very, very easy-going, yes, never ruffled, no, she ne-, no, neve
r seen her in a temper, not mother, no, father, yes. Yes, there was a mixture there, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Behave towards them? Oh, they expected us to behave, er, well, with dignity and, and
 courtesy, otherwise we'd be for it, yes, with me father, yes. When he told us to do a thing, we had to do it, at once, very strict bringing up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And if you didn't do it, then what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, well, then, er, then there'd be, er, thrashing of some kind, yes, smack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your parents bring you up to think of certain things as being important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, well, mother used to talk to us about different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, oh, when we get grown up and get married, you see, 
she used to talk to us a lot when we were quite young, really, seven or eight or nine years of age, yes, she was, er, practicing Christian, mother was. You'd to get the Bible out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you say that your ideas were mostly from your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, mother, definitely. She was a much more docile person than my father, er, altogether. He was quick tempered, but mother wasn't.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What was your parents' attitude to swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, no, no swearing, no swearing in the house, oh good gra
cious, no, no that was taboo, never thought about, we didn't, we didn't swear, we didn't do it. There was more, there was a lot more parental control over children than there are, is today, definitely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of things did you do together as a family, you\rquote 
re your mother and father stopped work in the evenings, and you were all in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, oh, when father stopped, oh, I see, well, some used to go out and some used to stay in, er, not much in particular, there was, we didn't have a, a piano, so we couldn't play the piano (..) \{BLANK\} so, er, we'd just sit and read; or talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would your parents read out loud at all to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no, er, mother, mother would read from the Bible out loud, yes, but not father, he used to, he'd, he'd si
t by himself and read in his own chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of things would he read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, er, oh, good books, er, he used to go to, er, men's Bible class and he used to get prizes and he used to read those, John Halifax, Gentleman, er, Ivanhoe, Scott's Iva
nhoe and one or two more that I remember we used to have in the house. We had a little, er, a small library in the house of books, Dickens' books etc. which we used to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you any magazines or journals in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, not very often (..) \{BLANK\} perhaps the morning paper or the evening paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were birthdays anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Birthdays were, no, no, er, things were, things were too bad to do, to do anything like that, very very rare. We knew, we knew our birthdays and we knew when, when it was coming around, but there was no special, er, fuss for that particular child, no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What about Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Christmas Day? Oh, yes, we used to, er, we'd celebrate Christmas alright, and, er, father, father used to, er, do himself 
well that time, he, he'd spend money on us, then, to get, er, oh, yes, er, a present each, and, er, other things, all the, er, the children have, the goodies, he used to buy that, oh, yes, he, he did us very well for Christmas, although, as I say things w
ere very poor some years, but other years they'd be better, and then we got more then, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would your parents ever play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no, 'fraid not, no. To serious, I think, the, er, the life was too serious, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You said you did say grace at meals..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 .. did you ever have any other family prayers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, mother, mother would in, er, in the house in, in the living room, yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 When would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 In the evening, oh, yes. Oh, yes, and, er, we were taught to say our prayers every evening, from mother, this was, ye-.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 When you were still at school were you ever taken out to visit neighbours or friends or relatives or anybody like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you repeat that? (Question rep
eated) Er, well, we used to go ourselves, without being taken out, er, yes. For instance, I used to, er, spend a lot of time at my grandmother's, my father's, my father's parents, my grandmother and my grandfather, and other, other, oh, other aunts who we
re married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 They lived locally, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
They all lived locally, but mother perhaps would take one of us if she'd been to visit, er, a friend or another relative, yes, we, er, were very friendly with our other relatives on mother's side and father's side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you see them fairly frequently then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 About every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes. Oftener than that, er, some of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you ever go out with just your father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 With my father? Oh, yes, he'd take me out, yes. He
's taken me out er, to, er, different places. Said, come along with me, we'll go so and so, yes, he has done that, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of places would these be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, perhaps out in the country, you see or to Hanley, and then buy something there, or, 
he'd have a sudden idea, and he'd say, well, come with me. We'll go to Hanley, used to go on a tram, and buy something there, he was very good at times when he had the money, but other times he, he had a temper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you ever have a family holiday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, never, er, never saw the sea until I was 20.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 That was quite old wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How would you spend weekends when you were still a school boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 When I was still at school? Oh, er,..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What would you do on a Saturday, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, well, we, we'd go down to market possibly, and, er, or do errands, do errands for mother or for other people for a, a little something, a penny or tuppence, over to the pawn broker's for anybody that wanted to go. A very poor district
, a very poor area, this was, it couldn't be, it couldn't have been much poorer, might have been one of the poorest areas in the whole of the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What about on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 On a Sunday? Well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you wear different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, if
 we had them yes. If we had them, but there was, there was times when there was no difference. We used to clean our shoes, special on Sundays and, er, er, cleaner collar or get a new collar if you had it or, or a best cap to go to Sunday School, yes, we d
id, we had a change sometimes, not always.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would your parents let you play on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Er, they weren't in favour of it, er, actually, we didn't do lot of playing on Sundays. We used to go more, after we'd been to Sunday School, we'd go for a walk and back for Sunday dinner, lunch and then to Sunday School again in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What about after tea on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, well, we used to invariably stay in, yes, 'cause mother didn't go out much. She'd nearly always got, er, well, youngster
 to look after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you ever go to anything on a week night organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, er, er, yes, er, the only thing, there was the Band of Hope, we used to go, one night a week, but I didn't, er, I wasn't, er, a member of any Boys' Brigade 
or Scout movement, but the Band of Hope we used to go to. That was on Friday evenings at our chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You mentioned that your father was interested in politics ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What about your mother, would she vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No. Mother, mother, oh, mot
her'd vote, but, er, she wasn't interested, no, never heard her mention, no, no mother wouldn't mention. Women didn't have, er, the vote (?), 'course, mother couldn't vote until after 19-, er -18, after the war was over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would your father make a point of voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, yes, he, he, he did. Yes, he said, er, everybody ought to record the vote, and I say the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Was he actually a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no, I don't think he was a member although he used to go to the meetings
. Oh, yes, he used to go to the political meetings, but, er, don't think he was a member as such In some places men felt they risked losing their jobs if they voted differently from their employers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did this apply to your father, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Er, I don't, I don't think so, although my father always used to vote the same, the same, er, politics as, er, as the bosses, oh, yes, he was a Unionist, yes (..) \{BLANK\} and I was just the opposite when I grew up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What would your father spend his evenings doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, if, if he was at home he'd er, set in (??) reading, er, more than anything else, or he'd, er, if he had any money to spare he'd, er, be along to the public house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would he actually spend most evenings (..) \{BLANK\}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, yes, he would, yes. Four or five out of the seven, yes. All day Saturday, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had your mother any interests outside her home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, not much, er, no, er, very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did she ever manage to (..) \{BLANK\}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Money? To (..) \{BLANK\}
 no. No, the only time my mother never saw the seaside, never went to the seaside, no. The furthest she went was when we went to, er, Swadlingcote, and that'd be about, er, forty odd miles away. I know, I heard her say she hadn't, (..) \{BLANK\} 
she never went to the sea, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were your parents members of any savings clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Saving clubs? Er, no, they didn't, they didn't have, er, much to save, really, if father had anything over he used to go in the pub and have his beer with it, but not savings clubs as such, very, very rare; perhaps mother'd have one at the (..) \{BLANK\}
 perhaps to pay sixpence a week to, towards Christmas.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Being the eldest of a large family, how did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did I
 get on with them? Oh, er, very well, oh, yes, they, er, they seemed to look up to me and knew I was the eldest, and, er, they did ask, er, advice 'cause I was the eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 As a child, did you play with your brothers and sisters or were they neighbours' children who were your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, neighbours, well I can go back to when I was three, I went to school when I was three and I, I used to play with neighbours, well I always played, I played with neighbours' children all through my, er, school days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Whereabouts would you play, in their yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, yes, their yard or our yard or, or perhaps in the, in the street, the street itself, or, or, in a nearby field, I-, if we lived near a field, which we did at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you ever have these children in your house, or would you ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, yes, they used to come, oh, yes, yes, they used, to, er, one or two perhaps come for me and I'd do the same to their house, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of games? Wel
l, er, when I was growing up a bit we, er, played, er, cricket and football, and running, a lot of running, we used to do, athletics, but we weren't members of any club, but we used to do it just for the exercise. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 Yes, there'd be, er, a lot of us, all prob
ably, er, all perhaps twelve or fourteen boys, about, from the age of about fifteen or sixteen, after we'd left school and started to work and got sixpence or ninepence or a shilling pocket money, and then we used to, er, (..) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 \{BLANK\} it together, and, er, somebody'd suggest, go somewhere, such a place, we'd go, walk it more or less, walk miles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 When you were still at school, did your parents ever give you any spending money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 Oh, no, no, never, we couldn't afford that, oh, no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Not even a penny a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, oh, yes, oh, yes, ah, but not daily, oh, only weekly, yes, about a penny, perhaps, yes, not much more than a penny, and I used to make up by running errands for other people, oh, yes, but nothing daily like they do today, perhaps tupp
ence, penny or tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, sweets, more or less, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 Did you ever go to the music hall or the cinema?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no, there wasn't, er, er, no, the nearest was, er, when we had the, er, cinema come with the
 fair, the annual Shrovetide Fair, er, they used to show the cinematographic pictures, well that was, that was the beginning of, er, of the cinema, that was, er, oh, about 1903, just about, before there was any cinemas opened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your mother ever have any help from anybody, from relatives or friends or neighbours in the house? Would they help her when ..?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh they went ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 .. she was having a baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Only, yes, when she was having a baby. See, perhaps one'd come along, but more, more ofte
n it, it was a, a next door neighbour, because in, er, yes, in, er, those days when people were very poor you'd be surprised how, er, how the neighbours used to stick together and help each other, because they knew, er, they'd be in the same boat any time
, so it, er, people were closer together, neighbours were closer together than they are today, yes..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your parents have any friends whom they would see regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Friends they used to see? Oh, oh, yes. Sometimes friends'd come our house, somet
imes they'd go to see someone, but, er, not a regular occurrence, not a (..) \{BLANK\} thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were these your mother's friends, or friends of both your mother and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, er, both sides, yes, mother had, mother used to have a friend come
 down when I was about, er, fourteen or fifteen, used to come down and see, she came down to see us nearly every week until she died, for many years, and we used to go to their house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were friends asked in for meals or would..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, well no, not
, not u-, not usually asked specifically to come for a meal, but, er, perhaps if, you've to, you've to drop in, you see, perhaps have a cup of tea or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would your parents ever manage to get out and see people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did my parents go out and see them? Sometimes they used to go, but not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Who would they leave in charge of the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, well, I, I was left in charge, er, and another brother, and, er, I can tell you a story about that, when, er, they both went o
ut separately and, er, I had the key}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485  \{BLANK\}
 had a key, brother said I'll have the key and dropped it down the drain so we couldn't get into the house, only by forcing the, we forced a window or the door, when father came home he couldn't get in the way h
e wanted, and he had to go round to the other, back of the house, and that startled him, then we got a thrashing for that, the two of us did. I was ten years old at the time, ye-. Yes, I used to be in charge, and my brother had the key from me and he, he 
playing about and he dropped it down the drain and couldn't get at it. Unfortunate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You've heard that many people split up society in this period before 1918 into different groups of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you do this? Would you say that you could split up people in your young day? Did they belong to definite groups?
