\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 We did wear it. Oh, yes. That was a, a school, actually it was an experimental school, er, a very good one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you like that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, yes, very much, yes, good headmaster, very good, very good staff, yes I used to meet them later, years after I got married, and they'd always stop and talk, ye-. My wife was with me when they stopped and talked (..)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did the teachers emphasize certain things as being important, like manners, or punctuality, this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, yes, yes, punctuality's a virtue, they used to say, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of things were they keen on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Ooh, strict on everything, discipline, discipline was strict, er, it had to be done in other words, what they said had to be done, ye-.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your parents ever show any interest in your schooling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, very 
little, well, they, they knew how I was getting on, but, er, I shouldn't have left when I did, but father made me leave to go out to work (..) \{BLANK\} I would have gone on to be pu-, pupil teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 It sounded rather a shame ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes. Oh, I won another scholarship, you see, when I was, before I was thirteen to go to college which (..) \{BLANK\}
 Trenton (?) Hall, only they didn't get round to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And that was the end of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were the children at Queensbury from the same sorts of homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, no, no, I was about the poorest, oh, no, they were nearly all, er, tradesmen's sons and daughters, er, from Longton and beyond, er, one man, er, I went to school with was the designer of the Spitfire, Mitchell, Reginald Mitchell and the
y were mostly, er, sons and daughters of, er, the tradespeople in Longton, which I've met later, in later years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you feel out of it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no, no because we had, there was five of us together, taking my case in particular, there was fi
ve of us and, er, I was the poorest of the five, definitely, and, er, so it, er, that wasn't mentioned, that we were all, er, friends and all pals, and we all went our different ways. I saw one only, er, last year and I hadn't seen him for nearly twenty y
ears, you see, yes, he lives at Lightwood in Longton and his son's a headmaster and another sons' a, er, high school teacher at Longton, they've done well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did they teach it at Queensbury, treat all the children the same or would they single out certain children for different treatment?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No. All the same, all the same, you went in for, er, all the same subjects, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of subjects were you actually doing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, ooh, we used to do, er, all the lot to a (??) curriculum (..)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were they different subjects from the other schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, yes, yes, the other, they taught us more in three years there than they did in, er, preceding seven or eight, oh, yes, wonderful, ten, ten years of age and, er, I went straight into French and
 algebra, you see, we had our own, er, gymnasium, we had our own woodwork shop, the girls had their own laundry and, er, and, er, cookery, domestic science, they had no, no other school in Longton had that. They had their own chemistry and physics laborat
ory, no other school had that, oh (..) \{BLANK\} couldn't go wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You were very fortunate going there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well that's what I say now. Late Lord (..) \{BLANK\} he died, er, few months ago, he used to go there, he was a the Lord }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 Mayor about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 , er, seven or eight years and his sister's the Lord Mayor now, Mrs. Robinson and he was, er, Sir Harold (..) \{BLANK\}
 well he went to my school, that's right. Have you enquired o-, o-, of the people who have been to Queensbury?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, I've met another couple who have been there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And what did they say, similar to what I said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 They said it was an excellent school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Where did these people live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 On the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Utoxeter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, oh, yes. Were they about my age? I bet I know them. Can you remember their names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, I can't. I can visualise them ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did the man and his wife both go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, it was a man and his wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, well, lot a lot of people went there married, you know, I met a couple, er, this year that er, went there, the same
 time as me, in, er, in our class and, er, she married, er, my wife was (..) \{BLANK\}
 Her name was, er Lillian Brown, she married Jim Quale, he was a tradesman, er, plumber and painter and several couples married from there. And they told you, they told you it was a good school, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 They said it was an excellent school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 It was the best there was in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Potteries{\*\xmlclose}
, marvellous what, wonderful headmaster, ye-.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You said you earned a bit of extra money by running errands for neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you any other part time jobs before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, yes, yes, I, I had a job at, er, the barber's shop on Friday, Friday night and, er, all day Saturday, er, lather boy. I used to get one and six a weekend for Friday night and Saturday, and I had my food with the barber's family. That was in the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Utoxeter Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Longton. I was, I was going to Queensbury then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you hand over that ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, well, I'd put it in the Post Office next door, which belonged, er, to the, e
r, the barber's mother kept the Post Office, sub Post Office, and I had a bank book, and, er, I used to put me one and sixpence in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You started saving up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well, I started saving it up, but one day my father said, you've got some money in the Pos
t Office, I said, yes, and he took the book off me, he had the lot, there was about two pounds in, so I didn't get it, then I had a newspaper round which I used to get one and sixpence, er, for morning and evening. I had that first and then I went to, er,
 the barber's shop and often (?) when I left school I left (..) \{BLANK\} brother to have the, the job at the barber's shop and the lather boy and he, he did it till he left school, ye-. Any little jobs we'd do for a copper, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, you'd earn a bit extra.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you spend it, or would you give your mother it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, well, if mother wanted it, she could have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I thought if your father was out of work ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Ye-?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 .. She must have needed any extra money ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Any extra, oh, yes, she did, she did need it, yes. Yes, I don't know, how we, er, survived really, it's a miracle how we did survive, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6037081\charrsid15749485 so many}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485  children (..) \{BLANK\} nearly everybody had a large family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 When you left school, you said you first worked as a saucer maker in a pottery ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Saucer maker on a pottery, yes. That was a ..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And after that it was a plate maker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 That's right, it was a platemaker, that's right, bit more wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Then you left the ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Pottery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 .. Pottery industry altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, well, I wanted to trade (train?) so I wanted to be a carpenter. There was no chance of getting a training in the potteries, only, er, saucer maker, or plate maker and I don't know whether I was, er, I f
ancied it really. I would have been out doors which I was in the building trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Weren't you frightened of it being a seasonal ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, well, not, er,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 .. you'd have been out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485  .. it was more or less a seasonable trade, but it didn't, er, (..) \{BLANK\} at the time, we used to, er, sort of take it as it came.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How old were you in fact when you started working as a builder's carpenter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Were you still at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I was still at home till I was, er, twenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I thought you left home a bit earlier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
No, when I was twenty, in 1914, then I went and lived with me grandmother who had another business then, she had a, she'd sold the coal business and she had, er, a cooked meat shop, yes, she had a cooked meat shop, in Fenton.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What did your parents think of your leaving home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
No, didn't, er, didn't say anything at all about it, but I used to go and visit me parents every week, or perhaps oftener than, er, once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 They'd miss your wage, though, wouldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, yes, I s'pose, well, others were coming on then, there was as many as three of us, or four of us working at once then, see, because I was, er, I was twenty then, I had, I had been working six years. Well, then, one broth
er was only one year o-, younger, another one was about six or seven so (..) \{BLANK\} gradually ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 They got started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes. They started to work, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You started work as a builder's carpenter ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How exactly did you find this job? Was it advertised or did you go and ask for it, or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Father spoke for me, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Which firm were you working for, a firm in Longton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Firm in Longton, yes. Builders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did he know them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Father knew them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of hours were you working then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Pardon. Hours? Oh, I was, er, in the summer months six o'clock in the morning until, er, five thirty in the evening in the summer, and then in the, er, fourteen weeks in the winter period seven weeks before Christmas t
o seven weeks afterwards, fourteen weeks, was, er, eight o'clock in the morning till half past four. Those were the, er, union building hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And you worked was it a six day week in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, five and a half, yes, er, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} till twelve {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}
midday{\*\xmlclose} on Saturday, when we used to get paid, er, no wages paid until Saturday {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday
{\*\xmlclose} when you knocked off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What were you paid in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, when I started? Er, threepence an hour or threepence ha'penny an hour, it's an hourly paid trade the building trade is, (..) \{BLANK
\} carpenters, the plumbers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Was this a fair wage, would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, that was a fair wage, er, for a boy, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did it increase?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, as you got older, ye-. Until when you're twenty one you, 
you see, you're a journeyman (?) then, and you get the journeyman's wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 It was like an apprenticeship then, in a way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well, yes, kind of, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What sort of a man was your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, he were very strict again. Er, if you smoked, 
you're not allowed to smoke, no although I didn't smoke, but that's one of the, er, rules that had to be obeyed, very strict, very strict discipline in, er, in the trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you get on with the other people that you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Alright, ye
s. Yes, as I say, er, when you, when you were young you had to, er, behave yourselves and, er, do as you were told, so that became, er, automatic. You didn't think of doing anything different, 'cause you were trained to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Then in 1914, you joined up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
I, I joined in, er, early 1915. I got married, er, we, we were married in, er, St. Valentine's Day, 1915 and I, er, I joined the army in, er, April 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How long were you in ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 I was in the army, er, almost four years till the January of 19-, er, -19.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Then what job did you come back to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Then I went, er, to see if there was anything in the building trade then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, yes, a bit, but not a lot, er, wages improved and then as the years rolled on from the '20s to the '30s it became very bad again, mm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 So did you leave it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Er, eventually, oh, yes, I left the building trade several times went back to it, er, yes, got a job as canvasser on, er, on all sorts of jobs. When I went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} I took me tools because, er, I went on to the building job again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 So that's been your major ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Well, oh, yes, well, as I say, if, er, if you're taught a trade, it always remains in good stead, see, you're a carpenter you can get a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you feel there was a great division between the trained craftsmen and the other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, yes, oh there was a division between, er, the labourers and, er, there weren't, there weren't a division of money much, 'cause, er, there should have been, I thin
k, personally, although, er, I know they, er, they have to go to the same shops, but, er, their, their labour wasn't so skilled, they used to get, er, 'bout tuppence an hour less, the w-, the tradesmen did, the bricklayers and the plumbers and the plaster
ers and the joiners used to get tuppence an hour more than the labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
What sort of a difference did starting full time work mean to you? Did it alter your attitude to your parents, or to your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, I, no, I, I seemed to, e
r, fall in with it all right, yes. No, didn't, er, didn't make any difference, I just, er, took it in my stride.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you still help your mother at all in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, even when we were working, oh, yes, yes, we were a very happy family, a
ctually, only father had a temper, but other than that we were always, er, very happy together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 After you'd started working, did you still go to Sunday School or Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, oh, yes, 'course we, yes, we did, ye-. Yes, went to Sunday School
 and we used to go to the outings of the Sunday School annually in the summer, they used to take us on a, er, Sunday School outing with a tea, yes..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you spend any evenings out away from home until you'd started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, from home altogeth
er? Yes, once or twice when I, I bought a bicycle, and, er, I cycled, er, different place and I did spend the night there. One, I, I remember going to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose} and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}
}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} from here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 By yourself, was this, or with friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, well, it should have been with, er, a friend of mine, but, er, he didn't go at the finish and I went on my own, so, er, er, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}, yes, that was, er, that was the first time I, er, saw the sea, the river {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Mersey{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, I was, er, ah, I said I was 20, I was 19, I think I was, er, 19 then, roughly 19, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 After you'd started work, did you make any new friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no u-, u-, usually they were the same, er, as you had whe-, when you were going to school, from the same, er,..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You stuck in a group, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
.. locality, Oh, yes, yes, the same, er, the same chaps I knew when I went to school we, er, more or less, but, er, as I say it was all very, er, friendly and, er, it wouldn't matter if you, er, went to anot
her group, they'd accept you, you see. In, in an area like this, built up area with thousands of terrace type houses people used to, er, seemed to stick together more, there possibly (?) a group on one corner, lower down the road there'd be another group 
of boys or girls and then they used to, er, play about together in the street, you see, but then suddenly someone'd say, well let's go to, for a walk, and perhaps go five or six miles and back again, think nothing of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Then it was that sort of thing you spent your spare time doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, yes, not, er, well, we didn't, er, we never used to go off with the, the girls, no, no, no, er, no, didn't, er, (..) \{BLANK\}
 us, somehow, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How did you first meet your wife, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well, she, she was in service at the shop next door to me grandmother's, er, cooked meat shop, that's how I met her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You would meet her frequently, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, er, used to see her every day, more or less, yes, nearly every day, and she was, er, er, the general servant at the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Was she from a local family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Yes, yes (..) \{BLANK\}
 she lived about, er, oh, no more than hundred yards from the, er, shop where she was in service, and, er, she asked me along to their house. I know when I'd, er, known her 
a short time and, er, she said, will you come and, er, meet our family and they had about eight in the family like we did, so, she'd made, er, some pastries cakes, herself, and, er, she's always been a good cook like that, you know, cook or pastry maker.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you go and ask her father if you could get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 No, no she asked her father, whether she could, er, bring me and there was no, er, (..) \{BLANK\}
 made very welcome at the house, and, er, my wife was the eldest in her family, she had a sister about two years younger and gradually (..) \{BLANK\}
 down till there was one only, er, er, born in 1914, the same year I met her, see, and, er, it was a little boy, but he died in the year the war finished, he was four years old when he died, so, it was a very happy family, er, my in-laws were, very happy.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did you get on with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Very well, yes. Marvellous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your wife meet your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, yes, oh, yes she used to go down with me, yes, oh, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your parents always meet your friends, either boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Er, oh, yes, used to meet, er, my parents used to meet, er, pals of mine, yes, but I didn't bring any girls, only, er, my wife, 'cause there wasn't any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Did your parents always expect you to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Oh, yes, yes, they, yes, they were pretty strict on that, er, roughly, er, nine o'clock in the evening, but sometimes, er, we'd go to bed, then get up again and then go out, yes, we've done that before ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Would you sneak out or ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
Yes, sneak out, come back again late at night, perhaps at the weekend when, oh, when I was, er, growing up about fifteen or sixteen or seventeen years old, you see, you get a little bit more independent then, because you were earning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Which of your parents, in fact, did you tell first that you were going to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Oh, I think my mother, anyway I told, er, both of them and they, er, no oh-, there weren't any objections, 'cause I was, er, twenty-one.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And you'd left home anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
And I'd left home, er, previous year, yes, I'd left home about a year when we got married, and, er, we only knew each other about, er, nine (?) months, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Had you saved up at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Er, no, not very, not much, not much, no, we hadn't saved up for the wedding, no, we'd, er, 'fraid not, we started from scratch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Where did you live when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Well, we lived, er, at, home, I'd left my grandmother's and went to live at another shop up beside, er, beside the road 
and we went to live there, er, greengrocers and a fruit shop kept by, er, an elderly couple, Mr. and Mrs. Bailey, and, er, we went to live there for twelve shillings a week, for the two of us I think it was twelve shillings a week, I think it was, I think
 so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Was it board and lodging? All in, or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Another voice) (..) \{BLANK\} board, Twelve shillings for the two of us.</subject2>

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) That's right, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 And it was all in, was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) Yes.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 How many rooms had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) Oh, we only had (..)</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Bedroom, bedroom, and then, er, (..)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) Er, yes, she was very fair, but of cou
rse they were just helping you out, you know.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Bit of housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) Do the washing for her, you know and ..</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) I didn't stay there long 
after my husband went in the army.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) She went back home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) Well, I didn't go home, no, I went to see him one weekend, to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}..</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
(Mrs. Stonehewer) .. and when I was there I got a job in a nut factory, stayed there for a, oh, how long did I stay there? Till he went abroad, 'bout a year wasn't it, something like that (..) \{BLANK\} such a long time ago. I haven't got such a good me
mory as he's got, you know.</subject2>
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 So you didn't have a home of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
(Mrs. Stonehewer) We didn't have a home of our own for twenty years after we were married, and that was when we went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. We couldn't
 get a house.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
(Mrs. Stonehewer) You couldn't get a house, all, all the while he was in the army I tried, and then of course the war finished there was no building being done and, er, then we went to stay with an 
uncle of his, his auntie died, and we stayed with him for, in that house, how long, about four years.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Five, five, six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) Four or five years, and we went to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and we \{BLANK\} went right into a new house, a beautiful new house.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Yes, lovely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
(Mrs. Stonehewer) But it was, we went, I went there for a week's holiday, and, er, we were walking round one night and we saw these houses and one was nearly fini
shed, my husband went to ask about it and he said, yes, we could have it. That was in the August, and I was down there in the September.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Yes .. yes .. yes, beautiful house, made of (..) \{BLANK\} nice, beautiful garden, well, we made the lawn ourselves.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
(Mrs. Stonehewer) 'Twas very bad to get a house after the first war, you know, very very bad.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 You had a long wait didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) Oh,</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs.
 Stonehewer) Now, you see they can buy the house, they can go in them straight away, can't they.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Oh, there's no comparison.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 
(Mrs. Stonehewer) Oh, goodness me, no, none at all, and they get far more money than we used to get.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) I find (?) sometimes we were born too soon, never mind.</subject2>

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198963 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mr. Stonehewer) No, not to worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11798551 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}K2{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12807994\charrsid15749485 (Mrs. Stonehewer) We've got (..) \{BLANK\} haven't we?</subject2>
\par }}